<task id="AIPU2-042" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build CompareDocumentsTool (structured diff between two documents)</title>
    <phase>2D</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-tool, documents</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build a CompareDocumentsTool AI tool handler that accepts two document IDs, fetches both
    documents from SharePoint Embedded via the SpeFileStore facade, extracts their text content,
    and produces a structured diff output broken down by document section. The diff must classify
    changes as additions, deletions, or modifications and group them per section. The output
    format must be suitable for rendering in the RedlineViewerWidget without further transformation.
    Follow the IAiToolHandler pattern and register via AIFunctionFactory.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with the SpeFileStore facade (ADR-007), text diff algorithms, and the Spaarke AI Tool Framework.</role>
  <goal>
    Given two valid document IDs, CompareDocumentsTool returns a structured DocumentDiff
    result that the RedlineViewerWidget can render directly. The diff correctly identifies
    additions, deletions, and modifications per section. Auth is enforced — both documents
    must be accessible to the caller.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/DocumentSearchTools.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-007-spefilestore.md to understand SpeFileStore usage constraints (no Graph SDK types above the facade). Read DocumentSearchTools.cs as a reference for tool registration and SpeFileStore integration patterns.</step>
    <step>Create CompareDocumentsTool.cs in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/. Implement as an IAiToolHandler following the DocumentSearchTools pattern.</step>
    <step>Define tool inputs: documentIdA (string, Guid format), documentIdB (string, Guid format), compareMode (enum: FullDocument/SectionBySection, default SectionBySection).</step>
    <step>Implement document fetch: call SpeFileStore.GetDocumentTextAsync for each document ID. Run both fetches in parallel (Task.WhenAll). If either fetch fails due to auth (403/404), return a structured error result indicating which document was inaccessible — do not throw.</step>
    <step>Implement text segmentation: split each document's text into sections using common heading markers (numbered headings, ALL CAPS lines, "Section X" prefixes). Fall back to paragraph-based segmentation if no headings are detected.</step>
    <step>Implement structured diff: for each section pair (aligned by heading similarity), compute word-level diff. Classify each change as Addition (in B, not in A), Deletion (in A, not in B), or Modification (changed text in both). Use a diffing algorithm (e.g., Myers diff or a simple LCS approach — do not import external NuGet packages; implement the LCS inline).</step>
    <step>Define DocumentDiff record: DocumentIdA, DocumentIdB, ComparedAt (DateTimeOffset), TotalChanges (int), Sections (list of SectionDiff: sectionTitle, changeType (Added/Removed/Modified/Unchanged), changesInSection (list of DiffChange: changeType, textA, textB)).</step>
    <step>Register CompareDocumentsTool via AIFunctionFactory with descriptive XML doc comments explaining inputs and output structure for LLM tool-selection quality.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: (a) two identical documents return zero changes, (b) addition in B detected correctly, (c) deletion in A detected correctly, (d) modification (changed word) detected correctly, (e) inaccessible document A returns structured error, (f) both fetches run in parallel (Task.WhenAll verified via mock timing).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>CompareDocumentsTool fetches both documents in parallel using Task.WhenAll.</criterion>
    <criterion>DocumentDiff output contains section-level grouping with per-section change lists.</criterion>
    <criterion>Each DiffChange is classified as Addition, Deletion, or Modification — not a freeform string.</criterion>
    <criterion>An inaccessible document returns a structured error result (not an exception) identifying which document failed and why.</criterion>
    <criterion>No external diff NuGet packages are added — diff logic is implemented inline.</criterion>
    <criterion>Tool is registered via AIFunctionFactory and appears in the session tool roster.</criterion>
    <criterion>All unit tests pass (dotnet test).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
